# Strings / UI text rules

## Requirement

- **Do not hardcode Vietnamese UI strings in components** (titles, labels, button text, table headers, empty states, helper text).
- Put UI copy in `src/lib/strings.ts` under `t.*`, then reference it from components.

## Scope

- Applies to:
  - Page headings (`PageHeading`, `Panel`)
  - Tabs (`TabsList`, `TabsTrigger`, `TabsContent`)
  - Tables (`TableHead`, `TableCell` labels/headers)
  - Buttons / CTAs
  - Dialog titles/descriptions
  - Form labels, placeholders, validation messages (except library-generated messages)

## Conventions

- Prefer reusing existing keys under `t.common.*` for shared copy:
  - `t.common.edit`, `t.common.period`, `t.common.status`, `t.common.visible`, etc.
- For feature-specific copy, add keys under the relevant namespace:
  - `t.stats.*`, `t.income.*`, `t.settings.*`, `t.budget.*`, `t.auth.*`
- Keep keys **deterministically ordered** (repo uses object key sorting rules).

## Exceptions (allowed hardcode)

- `confirm(...)` prompts and short one-off debug strings may be hardcoded temporarily, but should be moved into `t.*` once UX is finalized.
- Symbols only (e.g. `→`, `…`) are OK to inline.

